      "rendered": "20 Must-Know Fundraising and Social Media Stats"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/20-Stats-Nonprofits-Fundraising-Social-Media.jpg\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-18276\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/20-Stats-Nonprofits-Fundraising-Social-Media-300x300.jpg?resize=300%2C300\" alt=\"20 Stats Nonprofits Fundraising Social Media\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/20-Stats-Nonprofits-Fundraising-Social-Media.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/20-Stats-Nonprofits-Fundraising-Social-Media.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/20-Stats-Nonprofits-Fundraising-Social-Media.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/20-Stats-Nonprofits-Fundraising-Social-Media.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/20-Stats-Nonprofits-Fundraising-Social-Media.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a><strong><a href=\"https://think.withgoogle.com/databoard/media/pdfs/digital-non-profits-study_research-studies_1.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Google\u00a0research</a></strong> has revealed\u00a0a 30% uptick in searches\u00a0from August to September related to charitable giving. Your donors are currently in the process of deciding which organizations will be receiving their year-end donations. Thus, in time for the year-end fundraising season, below are 20 stats about fundraising and social media that every nonprofit needs to know. Overall, the stats indicate a continued upward trend in philanthropy worldwide, a steady increase in online fundraising, and mounting evidence that as the use of social media grows, so does online giving.</p>\n<hr />\n<h1>1. In 2014, 1.4 billion people worldwide donated money to nonprofit organizations.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.ongood.ngo/portal/facts-and-stats-about-ngos-worldwide\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18257\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/PIR-7.jpg?resize=600%2C600\" alt=\"PIR-7\" width=\"600\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/PIR-7.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/PIR-7.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/PIR-7.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/PIR-7.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/PIR-7.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><strong><a href=\"https://www.ongood.ngo/portal/facts-and-stats-about-ngos-worldwide\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source: OnGood</a></strong></p>\n<h1>2. 12% of all giving happens in the last three days of the year.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www1.networkforgood.org/digitalgivingindex\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18224\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/most-donations-made-at-the-end-of-the-year-2.png?resize=600%2C469\" alt=\"most donations made at the end of the year 2\" width=\"600\" height=\"469\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/most-donations-made-at-the-end-of-the-year-2.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/most-donations-made-at-the-end-of-the-year-2.png?resize=300%2C235&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><strong><a href=\"http://www1.networkforgood.org/digitalgivingindex\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source: Network for Good</a></strong></p>\n<h1>3. 64% of all donations are made by women.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/203154633168750817/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18220\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/women-donate-most-to-charity.png?resize=600%2C334\" alt=\"women donate most to charity\" width=\"600\" height=\"334\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/women-donate-most-to-charity.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/women-donate-most-to-charity.png?resize=300%2C167&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><strong><a href=\"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/203154633168750817/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source: Maximillion</a></strong></p>\n<h1>4. 72% of all charitable contributions are made by individuals;\u00a0followed by foundations at 15%, bequests at 8%, and corporations 5%.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.classy.org/blog/infographic-diversify-your-fundraising/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18218\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/72-percent-donors-individual.png?resize=600%2C367\" alt=\"72 percent donors individual\" width=\"600\" height=\"367\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/72-percent-donors-individual.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/72-percent-donors-individual.png?resize=300%2C184&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><strong><a href=\"http://www.classy.org/blog/infographic-diversify-your-fundraising/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source: Classy</a></strong></p>\n<h1>5. Matures and Baby Boomers donate most often to places of worship while Gen X and Millennials donate most often to children and youth development.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.abila.com/lpgs/donorengagementstudy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18262\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/how-much-people-give.jpg?resize=600%2C490\" alt=\"how much people give\" width=\"600\" height=\"490\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/how-much-people-give.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/how-much-people-give.jpg?resize=300%2C245&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.abila.com/lpgs/donorengagementstudy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>S</strong><strong>ource: Abila</strong></a></p>\n<h1>6.\u00a0Gen X donates more frequently than other generations.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.blackbaud.com/nonprofit-resources/generational-giving-report\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18231\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Gen-X-gives-most-often.png?resize=600%2C460\" alt=\"Gen-X-gives-most-often\" width=\"600\" height=\"460\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Gen-X-gives-most-often.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Gen-X-gives-most-often.png?resize=300%2C230&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><a href=\"https://www.blackbaud.com/nonprofit-resources/generational-giving-report\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Source:\u00a0</strong></a><strong><a href=\"https://www.blackbaud.com/nonprofit-resources/generational-giving-report\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Blackbaud</a></strong></p>\n<h1>7. 88% of dollars raised comes from 12% of an organization&#8217;s donors.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://bloomerang.co/blog/infographic-2014-fundraising-effectiveness-project-survey-report/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18244\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/donro-retention.jpg?resize=600%2C707\" alt=\"donro retention\" width=\"600\" height=\"707\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/donro-retention.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/donro-retention.jpg?resize=255%2C300&amp;ssl=1 255w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><strong><a href=\"https://bloomerang.co/blog/infographic-2014-fundraising-effectiveness-project-survey-report/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source: Boomerang</a></strong></p>\n<h1>8.\u00a075% of Americans think they donate more than average.\u00a0 In reality, 72% contribute at a rate below the national average.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.cambercollective.com/moneyforgood\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18253\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/DonorPerceptions.png?resize=600%2C334\" alt=\"DonorPerceptions\" width=\"600\" height=\"334\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/DonorPerceptions.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/DonorPerceptions.png?resize=300%2C167&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><strong><a href=\"http://www.cambercollective.com/moneyforgood\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source: Money for Good</a></strong></p>\n<h1>9. 84% of Canadians donate to charity with an average individual donation of $446 per year.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.ongood.ngo/portal/facts-and-stats-about-ngos-worldwide\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18227\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/PIR-2.jpg?resize=600%2C601\" alt=\"PIR-2\" width=\"600\" height=\"601\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/PIR-2.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/PIR-2.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/PIR-2.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/PIR-2.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/PIR-2.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><strong><a href=\"https://www.ongood.ngo/portal/facts-and-stats-about-ngos-worldwide\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source: OnGood</a></strong></p>\n<h1>10. 53% of Asia Pacific citizens donate to charity,\u00a0with those in Thailand (71%) more likely to do so and\u00a0those in Japan the least likely (16%).</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://newsroom.mastercard.com/asia-pacific/press-releases/emerging-markets-more-likely-to-donate-to-charity-while-developed-countries-give-bigger-amounts/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18207\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/charity-in-asia-pacific.png?resize=600%2C506\" alt=\"charity in asia pacific\" width=\"600\" height=\"506\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/charity-in-asia-pacific.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/charity-in-asia-pacific.png?resize=300%2C253&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><strong><a href=\"http://newsroom.mastercard.com/asia-pacific/press-releases/emerging-markets-more-likely-to-donate-to-charity-while-developed-countries-give-bigger-amounts/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source: MasterCard</a></strong></p>\n<h1>11. Volunteers give twice as often to charity as non-volunteers.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.volunteeringinamerica.gov/infographic.cfm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18229\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Volunteers-Give-More.png?resize=600%2C522\" alt=\"Volunteers-Give-More\" width=\"600\" height=\"522\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Volunteers-Give-More.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Volunteers-Give-More.png?resize=300%2C261&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /><strong>Source:\u00a0</strong></a><strong><a href=\"http://www.volunteeringinamerica.gov/special/Generation-X\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Corporation for National and Community Service</a></strong></p>\n<h1>12. Text donors are mostly likely to be 49 to 59 years old, female, married and a college graduate.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://mobilize.mgive.com/2014-mgive-text-donation-study\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18255\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/text-donors.png?resize=600%2C328\" alt=\"text donors\" width=\"600\" height=\"328\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/text-donors.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/text-donors.png?resize=300%2C164&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><strong><a href=\"http://mobilize.mgive.com/2014-mgive-text-donation-study\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source: mGive</a></strong></p>\n<h1>13. Email results in one-third of online fundraising revenue.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.salsalabs.com/get-know-us/blog/infographic-risk-and-rewards-sending-effective-emails\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18238\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/email-as-fundraising-3.jpg?resize=600%2C420\" alt=\"email as fundraising 3\" width=\"600\" height=\"420\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/email-as-fundraising-3.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/email-as-fundraising-3.jpg?resize=300%2C210&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><strong><a href=\"https://www.salsalabs.com/get-know-us/blog/infographic-risk-and-rewards-sending-effective-emails\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source: Salsa Labs</a></strong></p>\n<h1>14. For every 1,000 website visitors, a nonprofit raises $612.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.mrbenchmarks.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18234\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/average-online-gift-2.png?resize=600%2C578\" alt=\"average online gift 2\" width=\"600\" height=\"578\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/average-online-gift-2.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/average-online-gift-2.png?resize=300%2C289&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><strong><a href=\"http://www.mrbenchmarks.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source: M+R</a></strong></p>\n<h1>15. 17% of crowdfunding donations are made on mobile devices.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.kimbia.com/identifying-crowdfunding-donor-2014-donor-demographics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18210\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/demographics-of-crowdfunding-donors.png?resize=600%2C305\" alt=\"demographics of crowdfunding donors\" width=\"600\" height=\"305\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/demographics-of-crowdfunding-donors.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/demographics-of-crowdfunding-donors.png?resize=300%2C153&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><strong><a href=\"https://www.kimbia.com/identifying-crowdfunding-donor-2014-donor-demographics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source: Kimbia</a></strong></p>\n<h1>16. Nearly 1/3 of all online donations are now a result of peer-to-peer fundraising.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.classy.org/blog/infographic-the-value-of-peer-to-peer-fundraising/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18212\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/peer-to-peer-fundraising.png?resize=600%2C528\" alt=\"peer to peer fundraising\" width=\"600\" height=\"528\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/peer-to-peer-fundraising.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/peer-to-peer-fundraising.png?resize=300%2C264&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><strong><a href=\"http://www.classy.org/blog/infographic-the-value-of-peer-to-peer-fundraising/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source: Classy</a></strong></p>\n<h1>17. Pinterest and Instagram are now the fastest growing social networks.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.pewinternet.org/2015/08/19/the-demographics-of-social-media-users/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18247\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Social-networks-growing-the-fastest-2.jpg?resize=600%2C325\" alt=\"Social networks growing the fastest 2\" width=\"600\" height=\"325\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Social-networks-growing-the-fastest-2.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/Social-networks-growing-the-fastest-2.jpg?resize=300%2C163&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><strong><a href=\"http://www.pewinternet.org/2015/08/19/the-demographics-of-social-media-users/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source: Pew Research Center</a></strong></p>\n<h1>18. For every 1,000 email subscribers, nonprofits have 285 Facebook Fans, 112 Twitter Followers, and 13 Mobile Subscribers.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.mrbenchmarks.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18236\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/social-media-nonprofits.png?resize=600%2C432\" alt=\"social media nonprofits\" width=\"600\" height=\"432\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/social-media-nonprofits.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/social-media-nonprofits.png?resize=300%2C216&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><strong><a href=\"http://www.mrbenchmarks.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source: M+R</a></strong></p>\n<h1>19. 65% of all social media activity occurs on a smartphone.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/203154633168291567/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18240\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/mobile-social-media-traffic.png?resize=600%2C525\" alt=\"mobile social media traffic\" width=\"600\" height=\"525\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/mobile-social-media-traffic.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/mobile-social-media-traffic.png?resize=300%2C263&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><strong><a href=\"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/203154633168291567/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source: MobileCause</a></strong></p>\n<h1>20. 51% of people who visit your website do so on a mobile device.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/203154633168111715/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18242\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/responsive-design.png?resize=600%2C490\" alt=\"responsive design\" width=\"600\" height=\"490\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/responsive-design.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/responsive-design.png?resize=300%2C245&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><strong><a href=\"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/203154633168111715/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Source: Mobile Cause</a></strong></p>\n<hr />\n<p>To gain a better understanding of how nonprofits, charities, and NGOs worldwide use online technology, Nonprofit Tech for Good is conducting the first-ever <strong><a href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/2015NGOtechSurvey\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Global NGO Online Technology Survey</a></strong>. The data will be used to compile a report about regional differences in how NGOs raise money online, use website and email communications, and embrace social media. Depending upon your answers, completing the survey should take no longer than three minutes. Your participation is greatly appreciated!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/2015NGOtechSurvey\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18273\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/PIR-Report-Graphic-Newsletter.jpg?resize=600%2C200\" alt=\"PIR-Report-Graphic-Newsletter\" width=\"600\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/PIR-Report-Graphic-Newsletter.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/PIR-Report-Graphic-Newsletter.jpg?resize=300%2C100&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n",
      "protected": false
    },
    "excerpt": {
      "rendered": "<p>Google\u00a0research has revealed\u00a0a 30% uptick in searches\u00a0from August to September related to charitable giving. Your donors are currently in the process of deciding which organizations will be receiving their year-end donations. Thus, in time for the year-end fundraising season, below are 20 stats about fundraising and social media that every nonprofit needs to know. Overall, the stats indicate a continued upward trend in philanthropy worldwide, a steady increase in online fundraising, and mounting evidence that as the use of social media grows, so does online giving. 1. In 2014, 1.4 billion people worldwide donated money to nonprofit organizations. Source: OnGood </p>\n",
      "protected": false
    },
